 ('2', '2', 'en_us', 'Hands-on learning in small classes', '<p>Learn by working on the latest equipment with individual attention from professional instructors.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '95% of graduates get jobs.', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'See what we offer', '/programs', '2016-06-25 15:42:12', '2016-08-15 00:35:17', '0464df06-a73e-4cb4-a32f-3d4e92304887'),
 ('3', '3', 'en_us', 'We just installed Craft!', '<p>Craft is the CMS that’s powering Localhost. It’s beautiful, powerful, flexible, and easy-to-use, and it’s made by Pixel &amp; Tonic. We can’t wait to dive in and see what it’s capable of!</p>\n\n<!--pagebreak-->\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<p>This is even more captivating content, which you couldn’t see on the News index page because it was entered after a Page Break, and the News index template only likes to show the content on the first page.</p>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<p>Craft: a nice alternative to Word, if you’re making a website.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2016-06-25 15:42:12', '2016-08-06 19:52:12', '37489d4d-3a03-40cc-b0e7-b2e9d966ed28'),
 ('5', '5', 'en_us', 'Air Conditioning, Refrigeration and Heating', '<p><strong>The Air Conditioning/Refrigeration and Heating Program</strong> is focused on training service personnel for this field. The objective of the program is to provide a student with knowledge of the basic principles of air conditioning/refrigeration and heating mechanisms, their operation, maintenance, service and repair. A unique and vital benefit to Moore Tech students is the combination of classroom study with hands-on, working experience with modern equipment in completely furnished, individual heating lab and refrigeration &amp; air conditioning lab. Moore Tech professional instructors impart the knowledge that creates the ability that builds the confidence a student needs to be successfully employed in the industry. After completing the program the individual should be an employable, competent service technician.<br /></p>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<p>* Visit the <a href=\"http://www.mynextmove.org/profile/summary/49-9021.00\">O*NET</a> link or go to the Dept. of Labor resource center to view the employment outlook for this program.</p>', '<iframe width=\"560\" height=\"315\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/evz13Th2gBQ\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen></iframe>', NULL, '49-9021.01', '81', 'The Air Conditioning/Refrigeration and Heating Program is focused on training service personnel for this field. The objective of the program is to provide a student with knowledge of the basic principles of air conditioning/refrigeration and heating mechanisms, their operation, maintenance, service and repair.', '', 'Air Conditioning, Refrigeration, & Heating', 'Associate Degree', 'Two years (Six Trimesters)', '(CIP) Code: 47.0201 Heating, Air Conditioning, Ventilation and Refrigeration Maintenance Technology/Technicians', '(SOC) Code: 49-9021.01 Heating, Air Conditioning & Refrigeration Mechanics and Installers', '<p><strong>T</strong><strong>he college does not participate in any type of loan programs.</strong> For students completing the program, the amount of loan debt for program graduates is shown below:</p>\n\n<p><strong>Federal loans: none<br />Private education loans: none<br />Institutional financing plan: none</strong> (Students pay for each trimester before beginning the next trimester.)</p>', 'The Air Conditioning, Refrigeration, & Heating program is designed to be completed in 2 years. Forty-four (44) students completed the program between July 1, 2012 and June 30, 2013. Ninety-five percent (95%) of the graduating students completed the program within two years. This data includes all levels of program completers during the period: degrees, diplomas, and certificates. ', '<p><strong>What are the chances of getting a job upon graduation? The placement rate for students</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>completing between July 1, 2012 and June 30, 2013 was 71.8%.</strong> The U.S. Department of Education requires colleges to report data using the period shown above even though it is not be the most current data.</p>', 'The placement rate for students graduating in this program on that date was 81%. Students were typically placed in jobs as Air Conditioning and Heating service technicians. Placement rates are based on graduates who were employed within 180 days of completion. Completers were tracked by using completion surveys with a response rate of 90%. The college is accredited by Council on Occupational Education and has been for over 40 years.', NULL, 'The objective of the program is to provide a student with knowledge of the basic principles of air conditioning/refrigeration and heating mechanisms, their operation, maintenance, service and repair.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2016-08-06 19:48:12', '2016-08-15 12:31:42', '56192b95-ad51-40f4-9d39-ce5836397e74'),
 ('6', '6', 'en_us', 'Industrial Electricity and Plant Maintenance', '<p>Industrial Electricity and Plant Maintenance is designed for individuals who want to pursue the field of electricity as it applies to industry. Since the types of power sources vary from industry to industry, the program is designed to include as many of those sources as possible. Electrical, hydraulic and pneumatic and the appropriate controlling devices peculiar to each constitute the main body of the curriculum. Each is covered at length. Students learn hands on experience in areas such as electrical wiring-residential and national electric code, industrial electronics, industrial fluid power, electric motor control and other related areas of study. Students who elect this program should have a minimum background in mathematics, be able to use analytical analysis to determine cause and effect, and have good mechanical ability and dexterity.<br /></p>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<p>* Visit the <a href=\"http://www.mynextmove.org/profile/summary/49-2094.00\">O*NET</a> link or go to the Dept. of Labor resource center to view the employment outlook for this program.</p>', '<iframe width=\"560\" height=\"315\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/Qm_S9hLPouA\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen></iframe>', '2013-2014', '49-2094.00', '75', 'Industrial Electricity and Plant Maintenance is designed for individuals who want to pursue the field of electricity as it applies to industry. Since the types of power sources vary from industry to industry, the program is designed to include as many of those sources as possible. Electrical, hydraulic and pneumatic and the appropriate controlling devices peculiar to each constitute the main body of the curriculum. Each is covered at length.', '', 'Industrial Electricity & Plant Maintenance', 'Associate Degree', 'Two years (Six Trimesters)', '(CIP) Code: 47.0399 Heavy/Industrial Equipment Maintenance Technologies, Other', '(SOC) Code: 49-2094 Electrical & Electronics Repairers, Commercial & Industrial Equipment', '<p><strong>The college does not participate in any type of loan programs.</strong> For students completing the program, the amount of loan debt for program graduates is shown below:</p>\n\n<p><strong>Federal loans: none<br />Private education loans: none<br />Institutional financing plan: none</strong> (Students pay for each trimester before beginning the next trimester.)</p>', 'The Industrial Electricity & Plant Maintenance program is designed to be completed in 2 years. Ten (10) students completed the program between July 1, 2012 and June 30, 2013. Ninety percent (90%) of the graduating students completed the program within two years. This data includes all levels of program completers during the period: degrees, diplomas, and certificates. ', '<p><strong>What are the chances of getting a job upon graduation? The placement rate for students</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>completing between July 1, 2012 and June 30, 2013 was 80%.</strong> The U.S. Department of Education<br />requires colleges to report this data using the period shown above even though this is not the most current data. </p>', 'The placement rate for students graduating in this program on July 25, 2013 is 75%. Students were typically placed in jobs as Industrial Electricity & Plant Maintenance service technicians. Placement rates are based on graduates who were employed within 180 days of completion. Completers were tracked by using completion surveys with a response rate of 90%. The college is accredited by Council on Occupational Education and has been for over 40 years.', NULL, 'Electrical, hydraulic and pneumatic and the appropriate controlling devices peculiar to each constitute the main body of the curriculum. ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2016-08-06 19:55:08', '2016-08-15 12:30:05', '49412f07-b8e8-4777-b1a4-83b891b253b5'),
