 ('20', '20', 'en_us', 'Machining Technology', '<p><strong>The Moore Tech Machining Technology/Machine Shop Program</strong> has redesigned its curriculum to meet the needs of Memphis\' large and growing Medical Device Manufacturing industry. This program is taught in the most complete educational machine shop in the south with the most modern CNC machines. Courses provide the technical knowledge and fundamental experience necessary to perform machine shop work. Students learn to read and use blueprints skillfully, as well as hand tools and heavy machinery required to forge quality parts from metal.</p>\n\n<p>Once students understand how to make metal parts with manual machines, students learn how to make metal parts with CNC Lathes and CNC Milling machines using our state-of-the-art computerized CNC machines. Our new Precision Medical Machining course familiarizes students with the skills, documentation and requirements needed by the large local medical device manufacturing industry.</p>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<p>Moore Tech training provides students the experience of actually performing in a working machine shop. Each student is given increasingly more challenging assignments according to his/her individual progress and ability. Students may accelerate according to their skills. A technician in the machine shop trade should have sound work habits, knowledge of mathematics and blueprint reading and be attentive to detail.</p>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<p>With the growing Medical Device Manufacturing Industry in Memphis as well as the other manufacturing, construction and service industries that need metal parts, Moore Tech’s program provides a student with the hands-on ability and confidence needed for successful employment in these industries.</p>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"http://www.williamrmoore.org/programs/machine-shop/Machining-Brochure.pdf\">PDF Program Brochure</a></p>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<p>* Visit the <a href=\"http://www.mynextmove.org/profile/summary/51-4081.00\">O*NET</a> link or go to the Dept. of Labor resource center to view the employment outlook for this program.</p><p><a href=\"http://www.williamrmoore.org/sites/default/files/gainfulemployment/machine-shop-2012-13.pdf\"></a></p>', '<iframe width=\"560\" height=\"315\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/NZVLVHr0cdc\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen></iframe>', NULL, '51-4081.00', '100', 'The Moore Tech Machining Technology/Machine Shop Program has redesigned its curriculum to meet the needs of Memphis\' large and growing Medical Device Manufacturing industry. This program is taught in the most complete educational machine shop in the south with the most modern CNC machines. Courses provide the technical knowledge and fundamental experience necessary to perform machine shop work.', '', 'Maintenance Technology (Property Maintenance)', 'Diploma', 'One Year (Three Trimesters)', '(CIP) Code: 47.0399 Heavy/Industrial Equipment Maintenance Technologies, Other.', '(SOC) Code: 49-9042 Maintenance & Repair Workers, General', '<p><strong>The college does not participate in any type of loan programs.</strong> For students completing the program, the amount of loan debt for program graduates is shown below:</p>\n\n<p><strong>Federal loans: none<br />Private education loans: none<br />Institutional financing plan: none</strong> (Students pay for each trimester before beginning the next trimester.</p>', 'The Maintenance Technology program is designed to be completed in one year.', '<p><strong>Seven (7) students completed the program between July 1, 2012 and June 30, 2013.</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>100 percent (100%) of the graduating students completed the program within one year.</strong><br />This data includes all levels of program completers during the period including night certificates.</p>\n\n\n\n\n\n<p><strong>What are the chances of getting a job upon graduation? The placement rate for students completing<br />this program between July 1, 2012 and June 30, 2013 was 71.4%.</strong> The Department of Education requires colleges to report data using the time period shown even though this is not the most current. </p>', 'The placement rate for students graduating in this program on July 25, 2013 was 83%. Students were typically placed in jobs as Building Maintenance and Repair workers. Placement rates are based on graduates who were employed within 180 days of completion. Completers were tracked by using completion surveys with a response rate of 100%. The college is accredited by Council on Occupational Education and has been for over 40 years.', NULL, 'The Moore Tech Machining Technology/Machine Shop Program has redesigned its curriculum to meet the needs of Memphis\' large and growing Medical Device Manufacturing industry.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2016-08-07 01:44:10', '2016-08-15 12:27:31', '50131723-b033-4c49-8c26-988faefeb73a'),
