 ('28', '28', 'en_us', 'Plumbing', '<p>Plumbing is a three-year, nine-trimester program.<br /></p>\n\n<p><strong>When:</strong> Tuesday and Thursday nights 6:30-9:00 p.m.</p>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<p>Plumbers design, install and repair all kinds of systems for water, waste, drainage, sprinklers, steam, gas, heating and cooling in residential, commercial and manufacturing applications. Plumbers also installfixtures such as sinks, toilets, showers, bathtubs, dishwashers and water heaters. Plumbers connect all types of pipes and tubing, while following strict safety procedures and building codes.</p>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<p>Moore Tech\'s plumbing program teaches beginning students everything necessary to enter the plumbing profession. It also prepares existing plumbing employees to advance in the profession. Each student takes one course per term, a total of three courses per year, for three years, a total of nine courses before graduation. Beginning with the first term, Introduction to Plumbing, a student spends 84 hours each term in classroom and lab activities. Students learn all phases of plumbing, including systems design, appliances and fixtures, liquid and gas distribution systems, piping, soldering, brazing and welding, trouble-shooting and repair, reading blueprints and understanding plumbing codes.</p>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<p>For trimester dates, <a href=\"http://www.williamrmoore.org/admissions/academic-calendar/index.html\">see our calendar</a>. </p><p><a href=\"http://www.williamrmoore.org/sites/default/files/gainfulemployment/plumbing-2012-13.pdf\"></a></p>', '', NULL, '47-2152.02', '100', 'Plumbers design, install and repair all kinds of systems for water, waste, drainage, sprinklers, steam, gas, heating and cooling in residential, commercial and manufacturing applications. Plumbers also install fixtures such as sinks, toilets, showers, bathtubs, dishwashers and water heaters. Moore Tech\'s plumbing program teaches beginning students everything necessary to enter the plumbing profession. It also prepares existing plumbing employees to advance in the profession.', '', 'Plumbing', 'Certificate', 'Three year night program (9 Trimesters)', '(CIP) Code 46.0503 Plumbing Technology/Plumber', '(SOC) Code: 47-2152.02 Plumbers', '<p><strong>The college does not participate in any type of loan programs. </strong>For students completing the program, the amount of loan debt for program graduates is shown below:</p>\n\n<ul><li><strong>Federal loans: none</strong></li><li><strong>Private education loans: none</strong></li><li><strong>Institutional financing plan: none</strong> (Students pay for each trimester before beginning the next trimester.</li></ul>', '', '<p><strong>What are the chances of getting a job when I graduate?</strong></p>\n\n<p>This new program began in the current college year 2013-2014.<br />No one has completed the three year program during the reporting period.<br /><strong>The college is accredited by Council on Occupational Education and has been for over 40 years.</strong></p>', 'Plumbers', NULL, 'Moore Tech\'s plumbing program teaches beginning students everything necessary to enter the plumbing profession, or prepare existing plumbers to advance in the profession.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2016-08-13 13:18:21', '2016-08-15 12:27:46', '754239d7-4b7e-487e-99cd-4867590b2b07'),
