 ('12', '5', '4', '1', 'en_us', '2', '', '{\"typeId\":\"5\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Air Conditioning, Refrigeration and Heating\",\"slug\":\"test\",\"postDate\":1470512880,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<h2><strong>81% placement rates for graduates from this program.*<\\/strong><\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>The Air Conditioning\\/Refrigeration and Heating Program<\\/strong>&nbsp;is focused on training service personnel for this field. The objective of the program is to provide a student with knowledge of the basic principles of air conditioning\\/refrigeration and heating mechanisms, their operation, maintenance, service and repair. A unique and vital benefit to Moore Tech students is the combination of classroom study with hands-on, working experience with modern equipment in completely furnished, individual heating lab and refrigeration & air conditioning lab. Moore Tech professional instructors impart the knowledge that creates the ability that builds the confidence a student needs to be successfully employed in the industry. After completing the program the individual should be an employable, competent service technician.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>* Visit the&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.mynextmove.org\\/profile\\/summary\\/49-9021.00\\\">O*NET<\\/a>&nbsp;link or go to the Dept. of Labor resource center to view the employment outlook for this program.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.williamrmoore.org\\/sites\\/default\\/files\\/gainfulemployment\\/AC-2012-13.pdf\\\">Gainful Employment Information For This Program<\\/a><\\/p>\",\"2\":\"\",\"3\":\"\"}}', '2016-08-06 19:50:42', '2016-08-06 19:50:42', 'eaaa612f-44e6-42e4-84ed-b2e04893905b'),
