 ('136', '6', '4', '1', 'en_us', '10', '', '{\"typeId\":\"5\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Industrial Electricity and Plant Maintenance\",\"slug\":\"industrial-electricity-and-plant-maintenance\",\"postDate\":1470513300,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<h2>75% placement rates for graduates from this program.*<\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Industrial Electricity and Plant Maintenance&nbsp;is designed for individuals who want to pursue the field of electricity as it applies to industry. Since the types of power sources vary from industry to industry, the program is designed to include as many of those sources as possible. Electrical, hydraulic and pneumatic and the appropriate controlling devices peculiar to each constitute the main body of the curriculum. Each is covered at length. Students learn hands on experience in areas such as electrical wiring-residential and national electric code, industrial electronics, industrial fluid power, electric motor control and other related areas of study. Students who elect this program should have a minimum background in mathematics, be able to use analytical analysis to determine cause and effect, and have good mechanical ability and dexterity.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>* Visit the&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.mynextmove.org\\/profile\\/summary\\/49-2094.00\\\">O*NET<\\/a>&nbsp;link or go to the Dept. of Labor resource center to view the employment outlook for this program.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.williamrmoore.org\\/sites\\/default\\/files\\/gainfulemployment\\/plant-maint-2012-13.pdf\\\">Gainful Employment Information For This Program<\\/a><\\/p>\",\"32\":\"<p><strong>What are the chances of getting a job upon graduation? The placement rate for students<\\/strong><\\/p><p><strong>completing between July 1, 2012 and June 30, 2013 was 80%.<\\/strong> The U.S. Department of Education<br>requires colleges to report this data using the period shown above even though this is not the most current data.&nbsp;<\\/p>\",\"24\":\"(CIP) Code: 47.0399 Heavy\\/Industrial Equipment Maintenance Technologies, Other\",\"20\":\"\",\"31\":\"The Industrial Electricity & Plant Maintenance program is designed to be completed in 2 years. Ten (10) students completed the program between July 1, 2012 and June 30, 2013. Ninety percent (90%) of the graduating students completed the program within two years. This data includes all levels of program completers during the period: degrees, diplomas, and certificates. \",\"30\":\"<p><strong>The college does not participate in any type of loan programs.<\\/strong> For students completing the program,&nbsp;the amount of loan debt for program graduates is shown below:<\\/p><p><strong>Federal loans: none<br>Private education loans: none<br>Institutional financing plan: none<\\/strong> (Students pay for each trimester before beginning the next trimester.)<\\/p>\",\"7\":\"92\",\"21\":\"Industrial Electricity & Plant Maintenance\",\"23\":\"Two years (Six Trimesters)\",\"22\":\"Associate Degree\",\"27\":{\"new1\":{\"type\":\"question\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"How much will the Industrial Electricity & Plant Maintenance program cost?\",\"answer\":\"<p><strong>Associate Degree program cost: Tuition and fees: $ 13,335<\\/strong><\\/p>\"}},\"new2\":{\"type\":\"question\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"What other costs are associated with this program?\",\"answer\":\"<p>Books and supplies: $0 (Books and supplies are included in tuition and fees.)<\\/p><p>The typical electives selected by the student to go with this program do not have any additional fees.<br><strong>The college does not offer on-campus housing<\\/strong><\\/p>\"}},\"new3\":{\"type\":\"question\",