his\' large and growing Medical Device Manufacturing industry.\",\"6\":\"51-4081.00\",\"25\":\"(SOC) Code: 49-9042 Maintenance & Repair Workers, General\",\"33\":\"The placement rate for students graduating in this program on July 25, 2013 was 83%. Students were typically placed in jobs as Building Maintenance and Repair workers. Placement rates are based on graduates who were employed within 180 days of completion. Completers were tracked by using completion surveys with a response rate of 100%. The college is accredited by Council on Occupational Education and has been for over 40 years.\",\"19\":[\"102\"],\"3\":\"<iframe width=\\\"560\\\" height=\\\"315\\\" src=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/embed\\/NZVLVHr0cdc\\\" frameborder=\\\"0\\\" allowfullscreen><\\/iframe>\"}}', '2016-08-14 11:17:50', '2016-08-14 11:17:50', 'e74c67a8-bbbe-47d8-95dd-bea56c7dff07'),
 ('152', '25', '4', '1', 'en_us', '15', '', '{\"typeId\":\"5\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Maintenance Technology \\/ Property Maintenance\",\"slug\":\"maintenance-technology-property-maintenance\",\"postDate\":1471094160,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>The Moore Tech Maintenance Technology course provides a student with the technical knowledge and ability to perform repairs on, and\\/or maintenance of property (buildings, both commercial and residential), as well as knowledge of management concepts.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Maintenance Technology students will be taught numerous repair skills in electricity, plumbing and carpentry that will provide each student with a well-rounded background in general repair and maintenance. The course includes classroom instruction and extensive hands-on instruction and shop experience.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Introduction to maintenance involving carpentry, piping, and plumbing is included.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul><li>Safety in use of hand and power tools<\\/li><li>Measuring, layout and cutting techniques<\\/li><li>Dry-wall repair<\\/li><li>Repair of door locks, doors and windows.<\\/li><li>Pipe cutting and threading and use of PVC pipe.<\\/li><li>Repairing leaky faucets<\\/li><li>Toilet replacement and repair<\\/li><li>Cleaning traps and repairing leaking pipes.<\\/li><\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3>Property Maintenance - Management<\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Many students may be headed for a career as manager of a property maintenance staff. So training in management skills that include interviewing techniques, motivating and leading employees, preparing work schedules and preventive maintenance schedules, record keeping, inspections, parts ordering and inventory, and fair housing laws. Training in customer\\/tenant relations and communications that include writing reports, working with contractors and dealing with customer complaints.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3>Property Maintenance \\u2013 Electrical Repair (PM-111)<\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Residential electrical including safety, electrical theory, terms and symbols, diagrams, repairing circuits, replacing switches, receptacles, and circuit breakers, low voltage circuits and inspection.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3>Property Maintenance \\u2013 Carpentry Repair (PM-112)<\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Residential carpentry including safety, proper selection and use of tools, materials, measuring, cutting lumber, adhesives and fasteners, structural design, drywall repair, replacing locks and doors and residential inspection<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3>Property Maintenance \\u2013 Plumbing Repair (PM-113)<\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Residential plumbing including safety, understanding basic plumbing systems, materials, PVC pipe, copper tubing, soldering, faucet repair, toilet repair, disposal installation, repairing leaks and residential inspection.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>* Visit the&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.mynextmove.org\\/profile\\/summary\\/49-9042.00\\\">O*NET<\\/a>&nbsp;link or go to the Dept. of Labor resource center to view the employment outlook for this program.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>** Day program recommended electives include two courses in Industrial Electricity and Computer Operation.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.williamrmoore.org\\/sites\\/default\\/files\\/gainfulemployment\\/maint-tech-2012-13.pdf\\\">Gainful Employment Information For This Program<\\/a>&nbsp;<\\/p>\",\"32\":\"<p><strong>What are the chances of getting a job upon graduation? <\\/strong>The placement rate for students completing&nbsp;this program between July 1, 2012 and June 30, 2013 was 71.4%. The Department of Education requires&nbsp;colleges to report data using the time period shown even though this is not the most current.&nbsp;<\\/p>\",\"24\":\"(CIP) Code: 47.0399 Heavy\\/Industrial Equipment Maintenance Technologies, Other. \",\"20\":\"\",\"31\":\"Seven (7) students completed the program between July 1, 2012 and June 30, 2013. 100 percent (100%) of the graduating students completed the program within one year. This data includes all levels of program completers during the period including night certificates. \",\"30\":\"<p><strong>The college does not participate in any type of loan programs. For students completing the program, the amount of loan debt for program graduates is shown below:&nbsp;<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul><li><strong>Federal loans: none&nbsp;<\\/strong><\\/li><li><strong>Private education loans: none<\\/strong>&nbsp;<\\/li><li><strong>Institutional financing plan: none<\\/strong> (Students pay for each trimester before beginning the next trimester.)<\\/li><\\/ul>\",\"7\":\"100\",\"21\":\"Maintenance Technology (Property Maintenance)\",\"23\":\" One Year (Three Trimesters)\",\"22\":\"Diploma\",\"27\":{\"104\":{\"type\":\"question\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"How much does the Maintenance Technology program cost? \",\"answer\":\"<p>Diploma program Cost: Tuition and fees: $ 5880<\\/p>\"}},\"105\":{\"type\":\"question\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"What other costs are associated with this program? \",\"answer\":\"<p>Books and supplies: $0 (Books and supplies are included in tuition and fees.) The typical electives selected to go with this program do not have any additional fees. The college does not offer on-campus housing.<\\/p>\"}},\"106\":{\"type\":\"question\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"What financial assistance is available for this program? \",\"answer\":\"<p>Full-time students may qualify for: U.S. Dept of Education Title IV (Pell) Grants and Tennessee Student Assistance Corporation (TSAC) Grants.<\\/p>\"}}},\"5\":[\"26\",\"27\"],\"18\":\"The Moore Tech Maintenance Technology course provides a student with the technical knowledge and ability to perform repairs on, and\\/or maintenance of property (buildings, both commercial and residential), as well as knowledge of management concepts.\",\"45\":\"Provides a student with the technical knowledge and ability to perform repairs on, and\\/or maintenance of property (buildings, both commercial and residential), as well as knowledge of management concepts.\",\"6\":\"49-9042.00\",\"25\":\"(SOC) Code: 49-9042 Maintenance & Repair Workers, General \",\"33\":\" Building Maintenance and Repair workers\",\"19\":[\"100\"],\"3\":\"<iframe width=\\\"560\\\" height=\\\"315\\\" src=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/embed\\/ExliFFoeddY\\\" frameborder=\\\"0\\\" allowfullscreen><\\/iframe>\"}}', '2016-08-14 11:18:42', '2016-08-14 11:18:42', 'c6bb2571-5305-4922-9dcb-7b898e60fee9'),
 ('153', '24', '4', '1', 'en_us', '6', '', '{\"typeId\":\"5\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Welding\",\"slug\":\"welding\",\"postDate\":1470534600,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p><strong>The Moore Tech Welding Program<\\/strong>&nbsp;requires persons who possess good manual dexterity, good eyesight, and good eye-to-hand coordination. They should be able to concentrate on detailed work for long periods of time. Because welding processes differ and are used for a wide variety of purposes, the equipment welders use and the skill levels vary.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Job descriptions vary from highly skilled manual welders who can use both gas and electric arc welding equipment, and welders who plan their work from drawings or other specifications to those of unskilled welding machine tenders who simply press a button to start a machine. Skilled welders know the characteristics of different types of metals and can weld in various positions. Welders who build ships and maintenance welders are examples of skilled welders.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Moore Tech\\u2019s Welding Program is taught in one of the most extensive and complete welding labs in the south. It includes instruction in electric arc welding, plasma arc cutting, oxyacetylene cutting, oxyacetylene welding, (both ferrous, and nonferrous metals,) TIG (Tungsten Inert Gas) & MIG (Metal Inert Gas). The student is taught to identify and use various types of welding equipment, including the characteristics and techniques used in fabricating and assembling metal parts. An important aspect of the program is teaching the individual to read and follow directions.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>This program is designed for individuals who want to become professional welders. It provides the student with a working knowledge of the. The program also is designed to develop in the student the hands-on ability and confidence needed for successful employment within industry.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>* Visit the&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.mynextmove.org\\/profile\\/summary\\/51-4121.06\\\">O*NET<\\/a>&nbsp;link or go to the Dept. of Labor resource center to view the employment outlook for this program.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.williamrmoore.org\\/sites\\/default\\/files\\/gainfulemployment\\/welding-2012-13.pdf\\\">Gainful Employment Information For This Program<\\/a><\\/p>\",\"32\":\"<p><strong>What are the chances of getting a job upon graduation?<\\/strong> <strong>The placement rate for students<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>completing between July 1, 2012 and June 30, 2013 was 75%.<\\/strong> The U.S. Department of Education<br>requires colleges to report this data using the period shown above even though this is not the most current data<\\/p>\",\"24\":\"(CIP) Code: 48.0508 Welding Technology\\/Welder\",\"20\":\"\",\"31\":\"The Welding program is designed to be completed in one year. Nine ( 9) students completed the program between July 1, 2012 and June 30, 2013. Eighty-nine percent (89) of the graduating students completed the program within one year. This data includes all levels of program completers during the period including night certificates. \",\"30\":\"<p><strong>The college does not participate in any type of loan programs.<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>For students completing the program, the amount of loan debt for program graduates is shown below:<br><strong>Federal loans: none<br>Private education loans: none<br>Institutional financing plan:<\\/strong> none (Students pay for each trimester before beginning the next trimester.<\\/p>\",\"7\":\"95\",\"21\":\"Welding\",\"23\":\"One year (Three Trimesters)\",\"22\":\"Diploma\",\"27\":{\"114\":{\"type\":\"question\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"How much does the Welding program cost?\",\"answer\":\"<p><strong>Diploma program cost: Tuition and fees: $ 6480<\\/strong><\\/p>\"}},\"115\":{\"type\":\"question\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"What other costs are associated with this program?\",\"answer\":\"<p>Books and supplies: $0 (Books and supplies are included in tuition and fees.)<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Total fees depend on the elective courses taken. If Machine Shop is elected add $300 to the total.<br><strong>The college does not offer on-campus housing<\\/strong><\\/p>\"}},\"116\":{\"type\":\"question\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"What financial assistance is available for this program?\",\"answer\":\"<p>Full-time students may qualify for: U.S. Dept&nbsp;of Education Title IV (Pell) Grants and Tennessee Student Assistance Corporation (TSAC) Grants<\\/p>\"}}},\"5\":[\"21\",\"22\",\"23\"],\"18\":\"The Moore Tech Welding Program requires persons who possess good manual dexterity, good eyesight, and good eye-to-hand coordination. They should be able to concentrate on detailed work for long periods of time. Because welding processes differ and are used for a wide variety of purposes, the equipment welders use and the skill levels vary.\",\"45\":\"Instruction in electric arc welding, plasma arc cutting, oxyacetylene cutting, oxyacetylene welding, (both ferrous, and nonferrous metals,) TIG (Tungsten Inert Gas) & MIG (Metal Inert Gas).\",\"6\":\"51-4121.06\",\"25\":\"(SOC) Code: 51-41210.06 Welders, Cutters, & Welder Fitters\",\"33\":\"The placement rate for students graduating in this program on July 25, 2013 was 93%. Graduating students were typically placed in jobs as Welders. Placement rates are based on graduates who were employed within 180 days of completion. Completers were tracked by using completion surveys with a response rate of 100%. The college is accredited by Council on Occupational Education and has been for over 40 years. \",\"19\":[\"103\"],\"3\":\"<iframe width=\\\"560\\\" height=\\\"315\\\" src=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/embed\\/-AS1BhfQBHI\\\" frameborder=\\\"0\\\" allowfullscreen><\\/iframe>\"}}', '2016-08-14 11:20:59', '2016-08-14 11:20:59', '1bf6ad35-33e8-47f1-b36f-c0983a1a9679'),
 ('154', '28', '4', '1', 'en_us', '18', '', '{\"typeId\":\"5\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Plumbing\",\"slug\":\"plumbing\",\"postDate\":1471094280,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>Plumbing is a three-year, nine-trimester program.<br><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>When:<\\/strong>&nbsp;Tuesday and Thursday nights 6:30-9:00 p.m.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Plumbers design, install and repair all kinds of systems for water, waste, drainage, sprinklers, steam, gas, heating and cooling in residential, commercial and manufacturing applications. Plumbers also installfixtures such as sinks, toilets, showers, bathtubs, dishwashers and water heaters. Plumbers connect all types of pipes and tubing, while following strict safety procedures and building codes.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Moore Tech\'s plumbing program teaches beginning students everything necessary to enter the plumbing profession. It also prepares existing plumbing employees to advance in the profession. Each student takes one course per term, a total of three courses per year, for three years, a total of nine courses before graduation. Beginning with the first term,&nbsp;Introduction to Plumbing, a student spends 84 hours each term in classroom and lab activities. Students learn all phases of plumbing, including systems design, appliances and fixtures, liquid and gas distribution systems, piping, soldering, brazing and welding, trouble-shooting and repair, reading blueprints and understanding plumbing codes.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>For trimester dates,&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.williamrmoore.org\\/admissions\\/academic-calendar\\/index.html\\\">see our calendar<\\/a>.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.williamrmoore.org\\/sites\\/default\\/files\\/gainfulemployment\\/plumbing-2012-13.pdf\\\">Gainful Employment Information For This Program<\\/a><\\/p>\",\"32\":\"<p><strong>What are the chances of getting a job when I graduate?<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>This new program began in the current college year 2013-2014.<br>No one has completed the three year program during the reporting period.<br><strong>The college is accredited by Council on Occupational Education and has been for over 40 years.<\\/strong><\\/p>\",\"24\":\"(CIP) Code 46.0503 Plumbing Technology\\/Plumber\",\"20\":\"\",\"31\":\"\",\"30\":\"<p><strong>The college does not participate in any type of loan programs.&nbsp;<\\/strong>For students completing the program,&nbsp;the amount of loan debt for program graduates is shown below:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul><li><strong>Federal loans: none<\\/strong><\\/li><li><strong>Private education loans: none<\\/strong><\\/li><li><strong>Institutional financing plan: none<\\/strong> (Students pay for each trimester before beginning the next trimester.<\\/li><\\/ul>\",\"7\":\"100\",\"21\":\"Plumbing\",\"23\":\"Three year night program (9 Trimesters)\",\"22\":\"Certificate\",\"27\":{\"110\":{\"type\":\"question\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"How much does the Plumbing program cost?\",\"answer\":\"<p>Tuition and fees: $7695<\\