 ('174', '168', '15', '1', 'en_us', '2', '', '{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":null,\"title\":\"Associate Degree\",\"slug\":\"associate-degree\",\"postDate\":1471187995,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"8\":{\"new1\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"bodyCopy\":\"<p>William R. Moore College of Technology is now offering the ASSOCIATE of APPLIED TECHNOLOGY DEGREE.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The associate degree is available to any student in the day programs of:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul><li>Air Conditioning & Heating<\\/li>\\r\\n<li>Industrial Electricity and Plant Maintenance<\\/li>\\r\\n<li>Machine Shop<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Students enrolled in the associate degree program will have their clock hour credits converted to trimester hour credits. Upon successful completion of the two year trade program and the 15 hours of general education students will be awarded the associate degree.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3><\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3>General Education Courses will include:<\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<table><tbody><tr><th>Technical Writing<\\/th>\\r\\n<td>3 credit hrs<\\/td>\\r\\n<\\/tr><tr><th>Professional Development<\\/th>\\r\\n<td> 3 credit hrs<\\/td>\\r\\n<\\/tr><tr><th>Business Concepts<\\/th>\\r\\n<td>3 credit hrs<\\/td>\\r\\n<\\/tr><tr><th>Technical Physics<\\/th>\\r\\n<td>3 credit hrs<\\/td>\\r\\n<\\/tr><tr><th>Math for Technicians<\\/th>\\r\\n<td>3 credit hrs<\\/td>\\r\\n<\\/tr><tr><th>Total:<\\/th>\\r\\n<td>15 credit hrs<\\/td>\\r\\n<\\/tr><\\/tbody><\\/table>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>(One General Education Course will be offered each semester.)<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Important: ALL associate degree students MUST be high school graduates or have a GED. General education courses taken at other accredited post secondary schools may be transferable toward the degree requirements. The purpose of this degree program is to better empower you to succeed in your selected trade. <\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><a name=\\\"rankin\\\"><\\/a><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3>Moore Tech and Rankin College Transfer Agreement<\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h4>(Bachelors of Applied Science and Applied Management Degree)<\\/h4><p>Moore Tech students now have the possibility to transfer their training from Moore Tech toward a Bachelors of Applied Science and Applied Management Degree with Rankin College in St. Louis, Missouri.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Ranken Technical College in St. Louis, Missouri will accept transferable credits earned with a grade of \\u201cC\\u201dor higher from Moore Tech\\u2019s technical degree programs towards their Bachelors of Science and Applied Management degree program. Rankin\\u2019s program is offered as an online program that works out perfectly for student\\u2019s living in Memphis area. For further details, please <a href=\\\"\\/Ranken-MooreTechMemorandumofUnderstanding.pdf\\\">click here<\\/a>. <\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Moore Tech is accredited by the Council of Occupational Education. Other than the Rankin College Transfer Agreement, Moore Tech makes no statement or guarantee of transferability of credit toward other colleges. It is up to other colleges whether they will or will not accept credits from Moore Tech. Students interested in transferring to other colleges should contact the other colleges prior to enrolling at Moore Tech.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Sign up now to hold your place in this program.<\\/p>\"}}}}}', '2016-08-14 15:22:47', '2016-08-14 15:22:47', '515b2b7b-08aa-4c98-9dc3-bc18a2b104b6'),
 ('175', '167', '14', '1', 'en_us', '2', '', '{\"typeId\":\"15\",\"authorId\":null,\"title\":\"Diploma and Certificate\",\"slug\":\"diploma-and-certificate\",\"postDate\":1471188073,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"8\":{\"new2\":{\"type\":\"insertImage\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"rightAlignedImage\":[\"170\"],\"leftAlignedImage\":\"\",\"fullWidthImage\":\"\"}},\"new1\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"bodyCopy\":\"<h2>Moore Tech Diploma Program<\\/h2><p>Moore Tech operates 11 months of the year. The year is divided into three terms (trimesters) of approximately 14 weeks each. <\\/p><ul><li>Fall Trimester normally begins early in September and continues until the Christmas holidays.<\\/li>\\r\\n<li>The Winter Trimester extends from early in January to the middle of April. <\\/li>\\r\\n<li>The Spring Trimester normally extends from the middle of April until the end of July.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul><p>Day Classes are held from 9:00 a.m. until 3:30 p.m. five days a week. (Monday-Friday). Program length is measured in clock-hours, with all-day school programs, except Welding. Welding diplomas are awarded after some 1,200 hours or one year of full-time study.<\\/p><h2>Moore Tech Certificate Program<\\/h2><p>Night school programs qualify only for certificates, with six terms or 504 clock-hours required for each program, except Maintenance Technology and Welding, which only meets for three terms, or 252 clock-hours. Night classes meet two nights per week, on either a Monday &amp; Wednesday or Tuesday &amp; Thursday schedule.<\\/p><p>For additional information, call the Admissions Office at (901) 726-1977.<\\/p>\"}}}}}', '2016-08-14 15:24:12', '2016-08-14 15:24:12', '868758f3-c27c-40ed-a31a-4ee05fe569df'),
 ('176', '168', '15', '1', 'en_us', '3', '', '{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":null,\"title\":\"Associate Degree\",\"slug\":\"associate-degree\",\"postDate\":1471187995,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"8\":{\"169\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"bodyCopy\":\"<p>William R. Moore College of Technology is now offering the ASSOCIATE of APPLIED TECHNOLOGY DEGREE.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>The associate degree is available to any student in the day programs of:<\\/p>\\r\\n<ul><li>Air Conditioning & Heating<\\/li>\\r\\n<li>Industrial Electricity and Plant Maintenance<\\/li>\\r\\n<li>Machine Shop<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n<p>Students enrolled in the associate degree program will have their clock hour credits converted to trimester hour credits. Upon successful completion of the two year trade program and the 15 hours of general education students will be awarded the associate degree.<\\/p>\\r\\n<h3>General Education Courses will include:<\\/h3>\\r\\n<table><tbody><tr><th>Technical Writing<\\/th>\\r\\n<td>3 credit hrs<\\/td>\\r\\n<\\/tr><tr><th>Professional Development<\\/th>\\r\\n<td> 3 credit hrs<\\/td>\\r\\n<\\/tr><tr><th>Business Concepts<\\/th>\\r\\n<td>3 credit hrs<\\/td>\\r\\n<\\/tr><tr><th>Technical Physics<\\/th>\\r\\n<td>3 credit hrs<\\/td>\\r\\n<\\/tr><tr><th>Math for Technicians<\\/th>\\r\\n<td>3 credit hrs<\\/td>\\r\\n<\\/tr><tr><th>Total:<\\/th>\\r\\n<td>15 credit hrs<\\/td>\\r\\n<\\/tr><\\/tbody><\\/table>\\r\\n<p>(One General Education Course will be offered each semester.)<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Important: ALL associate degree students MUST be high school graduates or have a GED. General education courses taken at other accredited post secondary schools may be transferable toward the degree requirements. The purpose of this degree program is to better empower you to succeed in your selected trade. <\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3>Moore Tech and Rankin College Transfer Agreement<\\/h3>\\r\\n<h5>(Bachelors of Applied Science and Applied Management Degree)<\\/h5>\\r\\n<p>Moore Tech students now have the possibility to transfer their training from Moore Tech toward a Bachelors of Applied Science and Applied Management Degree with Rankin College in St. Louis, Missouri.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Ranken Technical College in St. Louis, Missouri will accept transferable credits earned with a grade of \\u201cC\\u201dor higher from Moore Tech\\u2019s technical degree programs towards their Bachelors of Science and Applied Management degree program. Rankin\\u2019s program is offered as an online program that works out perfectly for student\\u2019s living in Memphis area. For further details, please <a href=\\\"\\/Ranken-MooreTechMemorandumofUnderstanding.pdf\\\">click here<\\/a>. <\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Moore Tech is accredited by the Council of Occupational Education. Other than the Rankin College Transfer Agreement, Moore Tech makes no statement or guarantee of transferability of credit toward other colleges. It is up to other colleges whether they will or will not accept credits from Moore Tech. Students interested in transferring to other colleges should contact the other colleges prior to enrolling at Moore Tech.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Sign up now to hold your place in this program.<\\/p>\"}}}}}', '2016-08-14 15:24:50', '2016-08-14 15:24:50', 'b0090fff-9b41-4a63-b538-5a462285554f'),
