 ('179', '25', '4', '1', 'en_us', '16', '', '{\"typeId\":\"5\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Maintenance Technology\",\"slug\":\"maintenance-technology-property-maintenance\",\"postDate\":1471094160,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>The Moore Tech Maintenance Technology course provides a student with the technical knowledge and ability to perform repairs on, and\\/or maintenance of property (buildings, both commercial and residential), as well as knowledge of management concepts.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Maintenance Technology students will be taught numerous repair skills in electricity, plumbing and carpentry that will provide each student with a well-rounded background in general repair and maintenance. The course includes classroom instruction and extensive hands-on instruction and shop experience.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Introduction to maintenance involving carpentry, piping, and plumbing is included.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul><li>Safety in use of hand and power tools<\\/li><li>Measuring, layout and cutting techniques<\\/li><li>Dry-wall repair<\\/li><li>Repair of door locks, doors and windows.<\\/li><li>Pipe cutting and threading and use of PVC pipe.<\\/li><li>Repairing leaky faucets<\\/li><li>Toilet replacement and repair<\\/li><li>Cleaning traps and repairing leaking pipes.<\\/li><\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3>Property Maintenance - Management<\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Many students may be headed for a career as manager of a property maintenance staff. So training in management skills that include interviewing techniques, motivating and leading employees, preparing work schedules and preventive maintenance schedules, record keeping, inspections, parts ordering and inventory, and fair housing laws. Training in customer\\/tenant relations and communications that include writing reports, working with contractors and dealing with customer complaints.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3>Property Maintenance \\u2013 Electrical Repair (PM-111)<\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Residential electrical including safety, electrical theory, terms and symbols, diagrams, repairing circuits, replacing switches, receptacles, and circuit breakers, low voltage circuits and inspection.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3>Property Maintenance \\u2013 Carpentry Repair (PM-112)<\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Residential carpentry including safety, proper selection and use of tools, materials, measuring, cutting lumber, adhesives and fasteners, structural design, drywall repair, replacing locks and doors and residential inspection<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3>Property Maintenance \\u2013 Plumbing Repair (PM-113)<\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Residential plumbing including safety, understanding basic plumbing systems, materials, PVC pipe, copper tubing, soldering, faucet repair, toilet repair, disposal installation, repairing leaks and residential inspection.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>* Visit the&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.mynextmove.org\\/profile\\/summary\\/49-9042.00\\\">O*NET<\\/a>&nbsp;link or go to the Dept. of Labor resource center to view the employment outlook for this program.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>** Day program recommended electives include two courses in Industrial Electricity and Computer Operation.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.williamrmoore.org\\/sites\\/default\\/files\\/gainfulemployment\\/maint-tech-2012-13.pdf\\\">Gainful Employment Information For This Program<\\/a>&nbsp;<\\/p>\",\"32\":\"<p><strong>What are the chances of getting a job upon graduation? <\\/strong>The placement rate for students completing&nbsp;this program between July 1, 2012 and June 30, 2013 was 71.4%. The Department of Education requires&nbsp;colleges to report data using the time period shown even though this is not the most current.&nbsp;<\\/p>\",\"24\":\"(CIP) Code: 47.0399 Heavy\\/Industrial Equipment Maintenance Technologies, Other. \",\"20\":\"\",\"31\":\"Seven (7) students completed the program between July 1, 2012 and June 30, 2013. 100 percent (100%) of the graduating students completed the program within one year. This data includes all levels of program completers during the period including night certificates. \",\"30\":\"<p><strong>The college does not participate in any type of loan programs. For students completing the program, the amount of loan debt for program graduates is shown below:&nbsp;<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul><li><strong>Federal loans: none&nbsp;<\\/strong><\\/li><li><strong>Private education loans: none<\\/strong>&nbsp;<\\/li><li><strong>Institutional financing plan: none<\\/strong> (Students pay for each trimester before beginning the next trimester.)<\\/li><\\/ul>\",\"7\":\"100\",\"21\":\"Maintenance Technology (Property Maintenance)\",\"23\":\" One Year (Three Trimesters)\",\"22\":\"Diploma\",\"27\":{\"104\":{\"type\":\"question\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"How much does the Maintenance Technology program cost? \",\"answer\":\"<p>Diploma program Cost: Tuition and fees: $ 5880<\\/p>\"}},\"105\":{\"type\":\"question\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"What other costs are associated with this program? \",\"answer\":\"<p>Books and supplies: $0 (Books and supplies are included in tuition and fees.) The typical electives selected to go with this program do not have any additional fees. The college does not offer on-campus housing.<\\/p>\"}},\"106\":{\"type\":\"question\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"What financial assistance is available for this program? \",\"answer\":\"<p>Full-time students may qualify for: U.S. Dept of Education Title IV (Pell) Grants and Tennessee Student Assistance Corporation (TSAC) Grants.<\\/p>\"}}},\"5\":[\"26\",\"27\"],\"18\":\"The Moore Tech Maintenance Technology course provides a student with the technical knowledge and ability to perform repairs on, and\\/or maintenance of property (buildings, both commercial and residential), as well as knowledge of management concepts.\",\"45\":\"Provides a student with the technical knowledge and ability to perform repairs on, and\\/or maintenance of property (buildings, both commercial and residential), as well as knowledge of management concepts.\",\"6\":\"49-9042.00\",\"25\":\"(SOC) Code: 49-9042 Maintenance & Repair Workers, General \",\"33\":\" Building Maintenance and Repair workers\",\"19\":[\"100\"],\"3\":\"<iframe width=\\\"560\\\" height=\\\"315\\\" src=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/embed\\/ExliFFoeddY\\\" frameborder=\\\"0\\\" allowfullscreen><\\/iframe>\"}}', '2016-08-14 16:45:05', '2016-08-14 16:45:05', 'b40eb0e0-f7c4-4c19-9aac-075d929cb46f'),
 ('180', '20', '4', '1', 'en_us', '11', '', '{\"typeId\":\"5\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Machining Technology\",\"slug\":\"machining-technology-machine-shop\",\"postDate\":1470534240,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p><strong>The Moore Tech Machining Technology\\/Machine Shop Program<\\/strong>&nbsp;has redesigned its curriculum to meet the needs of Memphis\' large and growing Medical Device Manufacturing industry. This program is taught in the most complete educational machine shop in the south with the most modern CNC machines. Courses provide the technical knowledge and fundamental experience necessary to perform machine shop work. Students learn to read and use blueprints skillfully, as well as hand tools and heavy machinery required to forge quality parts from metal.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Once students understand how to make metal parts with manual machines, students learn how to make metal parts with CNC Lathes and CNC Milling machines using our state-of-the-art computerized CNC machines. Our new Precision Medical Machining course familiarizes students with the skills, documentation and requirements needed by the large local medical device manufacturing industry.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Moore Tech training provides students the experience of actually performing in a working machine shop. Each student is given increasingly more challenging assignments according to his\\/her individual progress and ability. Students may accelerate according to their skills. A technician in the machine shop trade should have sound work habits, knowledge of mathematics and blueprint reading and be attentive to detail.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>With the growing Medical Device Manufacturing Industry in Memphis as well as the other manufacturing, construction and service industries that need metal parts, Moore Tech\\u2019s program provides a student with the hands-on ability and confidence needed for successful employment in these industries.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.williamrmoore.org\\/programs\\/machine-shop\\/Machining-Brochure.pdf\\\">PDF Program Brochure<\\/a><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>* Visit the&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.mynextmove.org\\/profile\\/summary\\/51-4081.00\\\">O*NET<\\/a>&nbsp;link or go to the Dept. of Labor resource center to view the employment outlook for this program.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.williamrmoore.org\\/sites\\/default\\/files\\/gainfulemployment\\/machine-shop-2012-13.pdf\\\">Gainful Employment Information For This Program<\\/a><\\/p>\",\"32\":\"<p><strong>Seven (7) students completed the program between July 1, 2012 and June 30, 2013.<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>100 percent (100%) of the graduating students completed the program within one year.<\\/strong><br>This data includes all levels of program completers during the period including night certificates.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>What are the chances of getting a job upon graduation? The placement rate for students completing<br>this program between July 1, 2012 and June 30, 2013 was 71.4%.<\\/strong> The Department of Education requires&nbsp;colleges to report data using the time period shown even though this is not the most current.&nbsp;<\\/p>\",\"24\":\"(CIP) Code: 47.0399 Heavy\\/Industrial Equipment Maintenance Technologies, Other.\",\"20\":\"\",\"31\":\"The Maintenance Technology program is designed to be completed in one year.\",\"30\":\"<p><strong>The college does not participate in any type of loan programs.<\\/strong> For students completing the program,&nbsp;the amount of loan debt for program graduates is shown below:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>Federal loans: none<br>Private education loans: none<br>Institutional financing plan: none<\\/strong> (Students pay for each trimester before beginning the next trimester.<\\/p>\",\"7\":\"100\",\"21\":\"Maintenance Technology (Property Maintenance)\",\"23\":\"One Year (Three Trimesters)\",\"22\":\"Diploma\",\"27\":{\"107\":{\"type\":\"question\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"How much does the Maintenance Technology program cost?\",\"answer\":\"<p><strong>Diploma program Cost: Tuition and fees: $ 5880<\\/strong><\\/p>\"}},\"108\":{\"type\":\"question\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"What other costs are associated with this program?\",\"answer\":\"<p>Books and supplies: $0 (Books and supplies are included in tuition and fees.)<br>The typical electives selected to go with this program do not have any additional fees.<br><strong>The college does not offer on-campus housing<\\/strong><\\/p>\"}},\"109\":{\"type\":\"question\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"What financial assistance is available for this program?\",\"answer\":\"<p>Full-time students may qualify for: U.S. Dept<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>of Education Title IV (Pell) Grants and Tennessee Student Assistance Corporation (TSAC) Grants.<\\/p>\"}}},\"5\":[\"17\",\"18\",\"19\"],\"18\":\"The Moore Tech Machining Technology\\/Machine Shop Program has redesigned its curriculum to meet the needs of Memphis\' large and growing Medical Device Manufacturing industry. This program is taught in the most complete educational machine shop in the south with the most modern CNC machines. Courses provide the technical knowledge and fundamental experience necessary to perform machine shop work.\",\"45\":\"The Moore Tech Machining Technology\\/Machine Shop Program has redesigned its curriculum to meet the needs of Memphis\' large and growing Medical Device Manufacturing industry.\",\"6\":\"51-4081.00\",\"25\":\"(SOC) Code: 49-9042 Maintenance & Repair Workers, General\",\"33\":\"The placement rate for students graduating in this program on July 25, 2013 was 83%. Students were typically placed in jobs as Building Maintenance and Repair workers. Placement rates are based on graduates who were employed within 180 days of completion. Completers were tracked by using completion surveys with a response rate of 100%. The college is accredited by Council on Occupational Education and has been for over 40 years.\",\"19\":[\"102\"],\"3\":\"<iframe width=\\\"560\\\" height=\\\"315\\\" src=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/embed\\/NZVLVHr0cdc\\\" frameborder=\\\"0\\\" allowfullscreen><\\/iframe>\"}}', '2016-08-14 16:45:18', '2016-08-14 16:45:18', 'f7e6fd23-f5b9-45dd-ae78-04eb9c6ab062'),
