 ('185', '168', '15', '1', 'en_us', '6', '', '{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":null,\"title\":\"Associate Degree\",\"slug\":\"associate-degree\",\"postDate\":1471187995,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"8\":{\"169\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"bodyCopy\":\"<p>William R. Moore College of Technology is now offering the ASSOCIATE of APPLIED TECHNOLOGY DEGREE.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>The associate degree is available to any student in the day programs of:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul><li>Air Conditioning & Heating<\\/li>\\r\\n<li>Industrial Electricity and Plant Maintenance<\\/li>\\r\\n<li>Machine Shop<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n<p>Students enrolled in the associate degree program will have their clock hour credits converted to trimester hour credits. Upon successful completion of the two year trade program and the 15 hours of general education students will be awarded the associate degree.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2>General Education Courses will include:<\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t\\r\\n<li><strong>Technical Writing<\\/strong> <span>3 credit hrs<\\/span><\\/li>\\r\\n<li><strong>Professional Development<\\/strong> <span> 3 credit hrs<\\/span><\\/li>\\r\\n<li><strong>Business Concepts<\\/strong> <span>3 credit hrs<\\/span><\\/li>\\r\\n<li><strong>Technical Physics<\\/strong> <span>3 credit hrs<\\/span><\\/li>\\r\\n<li><strong>Math for Technicians<\\/strong> <span>3 credit hrs<\\/span><\\/li>\\r\\n<li><strong>Total:<\\/strong> <span>15 credit hrs<\\/span><\\/li>\\r\\n\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>(One General Education Course will be offered each semester.)<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Important: ALL associate degree students MUST be high school graduates or have a GED. General education courses taken at other accredited post secondary schools may be transferable toward the degree requirements. The purpose of this degree program is to better empower you to succeed in your selected trade. <\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2>Moore Tech and Rankin College Transfer Agreement<\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3>(Bachelors of Applied Science and Applied Management Degree)<\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Moore Tech students now have the possibility to transfer their training from Moore Tech toward a Bachelors of Applied Science and Applied Management Degree with Rankin College in St. Louis, Missouri.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Ranken Technical College in St. Louis, Missouri will accept transferable credits earned with a grade of \\u201cC\\u201dor higher from Moore Tech\\u2019s technical degree programs towards their Bachelors of Science and Applied Management degree program. Rankin\\u2019s program is offered as an online program that works out perfectly for student\\u2019s living in Memphis area. For further details, please <a href=\\\"\\/Ranken-MooreTechMemorandumofUnderstanding.pdf\\\">click here<\\/a>. <\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Moore Tech is accredited by the Council of Occupational Education. Other than the Rankin College Transfer Agreement, Moore Tech makes no statement or guarantee of transferability of credit toward other colleges. It is up to other colleges whether they will or will not accept credits from Moore Tech. Students interested in transferring to other colleges should contact the other colleges prior to enrolling at Moore Tech.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/10.0.0.100:8888\\/admissions\\/enrollment-steps#entry:160:url\\\">Sign up now to hold your place in this program.<\\/a><\\/p>\"}}}}}', '2016-08-15 00:49:42', '2016-08-15 00:49:42', '5eb79651-1ecc-49f8-bf43-28bd2ec64bef'),
 ('186', '168', '15', '1', 'en_us', '7', '', '{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":null,\"title\":\"Associate Degree\",\"slug\":\"associate-degree\",\"postDate\":1471187995,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"8\":{\"169\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"bodyCopy\":\"<p>William R. Moore College of Technology is now offering the ASSOCIATE of APPLIED TECHNOLOGY DEGREE.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The associate degree is available to any student in the day programs of:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul><li>Air Conditioning & Heating<\\/li>\\r\\n<li>Industrial Electricity and Plant Maintenance<\\/li>\\r\\n<li>Machine Shop<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Students enrolled in the associate degree program will have their clock hour credits converted to trimester hour credits. Upon successful completion of the two year trade program and the 15 hours of general education students will be awarded the associate degree.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2>General Education Courses will include:<\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul><li><strong>Technical Writing<\\/strong> 3 credit hrs<\\/li>\\r\\n<li><strong>Professional Development<\\/strong>  3 credit hrs<\\/li>\\r\\n<li><strong>Business Concepts<\\/strong> 3 credit hrs<\\/li>\\r\\n<li><strong>Technical Physics<\\/strong> 3 credit hrs<\\/li>\\r\\n<li><strong>Math for Technicians<\\/strong> 3 credit hrs<\\/li>\\r\\n<li><strong>Total:<\\/strong> 15 credit hrs<\\/li>\\r\\n\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>(One General Education Course will be offered each semester.)<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><em><strong>Important: <\\/strong>ALL associate degree students MUST be high school graduates or have a GED. General education courses taken at other accredited post secondary schools may be transferable toward the degree requirements. The purpose of this degree program is to better empower you to succeed in your selected trade.<\\/em> <\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2>Moore Tech and Rankin College Transfer Agreement<\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3>(Bachelors of Applied Science and Applied Management Degree)<\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Moore Tech students now have the possibility to transfer their training from Moore Tech toward a Bachelors of Applied Science and Applied Management Degree with Rankin College in St. Louis, Missouri.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Ranken Technical College in St. Louis, Missouri will accept transferable credits earned with a grade of \\u201cC\\u201dor higher from Moore Tech\\u2019s technical degree programs towards their Bachelors of Science and Applied Management degree program. Rankin\\u2019s program is offered as an online program that works out perfectly for student\\u2019s living in Memphis area. For further details, please <a href=\\\"\\/Ranken-MooreTechMemorandumofUnderstanding.pdf\\\">click here<\\/a>. <\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Moore Tech is accredited by the Council of Occupational Education. Other than the Rankin College Transfer Agreement, Moore Tech makes no statement or guarantee of transferability of credit toward other colleges. It is up to other colleges whether they will or will not accept credits from Moore Tech. Students interested in transferring to other colleges should contact the other colleges prior to enrolling at Moore Tech.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/10.0.0.100:8888\\/admissions\\/enrollment-steps#entry:160:url\\\">Sign up now to hold your place in this program.<\\/a><\\/p>\"}}}}}', '2016-08-15 00:51:42', '2016-08-15 00:51:42', 'f759fc8a-eeac-42a6-ac08-95109ae93fc3'),
 ('187', '25', '4', '1', 'en_us', '17', '', '{\"typeId\":\"5\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Maintenance Technology\",\"slug\":\"maintenance-technology-property-maintenance\",\"postDate\":1471094160,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>The Moore Tech Maintenance Technology course provides a student with the technical knowledge and ability to perform repairs on, and\\/or maintenance of property (buildings, both commercial and residential), as well as knowledge of management concepts.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Maintenance Technology students will be taught numerous repair skills in electricity, plumbing and carpentry that will provide each student with a well-rounded background in general repair and maintenance. The course includes classroom instruction and extensive hands-on instruction and shop experience.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Introduction to maintenance involving carpentry, piping, and plumbing is included.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul><li>Safety in use of hand and power tools<\\/li><li>Measuring, layout and cutting techniques<\\/li><li>Dry-wall repair<\\/li><li>Repair of door locks, doors and windows.<\\/li><li>Pipe cutting and threading and use of PVC pipe.<\\/li><li>Repairing leaky faucets<\\/li><li>Toilet replacement and repair<\\/li><li>Cleaning traps and repairing leaking pipes.<\\/li><\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3>Property Maintenance - Management<\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Many students may be headed for a career as manager of a property maintenance staff. So training in management skills that include interviewing techniques, motivating and leading employees, preparing work schedules and preventive maintenance schedules, record keeping, inspections, parts ordering and inventory, and fair housing laws. Training in customer\\/tenant relations and communications that include writing reports, working with contractors and dealing with customer complaints.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3>Property Maintenance \\u2013 Electrical Repair (PM-111)<\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Residential electrical including safety, electrical theory, terms and symbols, diagrams, repairing circuits, replacing switches, receptacles, and circuit breakers, low voltage circuits and inspection.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3>Property Maintenance \\u2013 Carpentry Repair (PM-112)<\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Residential carpentry including safety, proper selection and use of tools, materials, measuring, cutting lumber, adhesives and fasteners, structural design, drywall repair, replacing locks and doors and residential inspection<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3>Property Maintenance \\u2013 Plumbing Repair (PM-113)<\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Residential plumbing including safety, understanding basic plumbing systems, materials, PVC pipe, copper tubing, soldering, faucet repair, toilet repair, disposal installation, repairing leaks and residential inspection.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>* Visit the&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.mynextmove.org\\/profile\\/summary\\/49-9042.00\\\">O*NET<\\/a>&nbsp;link or go to the Dept. of Labor resource center to view the employment outlook for this program.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>** Day program recommended electives include two courses in Industrial Electricity and Computer Operation.&nbsp;<\\/p>\",\"32\":\"<p><strong>What are the chances of getting a job upon graduation? <\\/strong>The placement rate for students completing&nbsp;this program between July 1, 2012 and June 30, 2013 was 71.4%. The Department of Education requires&nbsp;colleges to report data using the time period shown even though this is not the most current.&nbsp;<\\/p>\",\"24\":\"(CIP) Code: 47.0399 Heavy\\/Industrial Equipment Maintenance Technologies, Other. \",\"20\":\"\",\"31\":\"Seven (7) students completed the program between July 1, 2012 and June 30, 2013. 100 percent (100%) of the graduating students completed the program within one year. This data includes all levels of program completers during the period including night certificates. \",\"30\":\"<p><strong>The college does not participate in any type of loan programs. For students completing the program, the amount of loan debt for program graduates is shown below:&nbsp;<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul><li><strong>Federal loans: none&nbsp;<\\/strong><\\/li><li><strong>Private education loans: none<\\/strong>&nbsp;<\\/li><li><strong>Institutional financing plan: none<\\/strong> (Students pay for each trimester before beginning the next trimester.)<\\/li><\\/ul>\",\"7\":\"100\",\"21\":\"Maintenance Technology (Property Maintenance)\",\"23\":\" One Year (Three Trimesters)\",\"22\":\"Diploma\",\"27\":{\"104\":{\"type\":\"question\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"How much does the Maintenance Technology program cost? \",\"answer\":\"<p>Diploma program Cost: Tuition and fees: $ 5880<\\/p>\"}},\"105\":{\"type\":\"question\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"What other costs are associated with this program? \",\"answer\":\"<p>Books and supplies: $0 (Books and supplies are included in tuition and fees.) The typical electives selected to go with this program do not have any additional fees. The college does not offer on-campus housing.<\\/p>\"}},\"106\":{\"type\":\"question\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"What financial assistance is available for this program? \",\"answer\":\"<p>Full-time students may qualify for: U.S. Dept of Education Title IV (Pell) Grants and Tennessee Student Assistance Corporation (TSAC) Grants.<\\/p>\"}}},\"5\":[\"26\",\"27\"],\"1