ng industry.\",\"6\":\"51-4081.00\",\"25\":\"(SOC) Code: 49-9042 Maintenance & Repair Workers, General\",\"33\":\"The placement rate for students graduating in this program on July 25, 2013 was 83%. Students were typically placed in jobs as Building Maintenance and Repair workers. Placement rates are based on graduates who were employed within 180 days of completion. Completers were tracked by using completion surveys with a response rate of 100%. The college is accredited by Council on Occupational Education and has been for over 40 years.\",\"19\":[\"102\"],\"3\":\"<iframe width=\\\"560\\\" height=\\\"315\\\" src=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/embed\\/NZVLVHr0cdc\\\" frameborder=\\\"0\\\" allowfullscreen><\\/iframe>\"}}', '2016-08-15 12:27:31', '2016-08-15 12:27:31', '8b2508d2-8b1b-46ca-8d14-9dc725920c45'),
 ('192', '28', '4', '1', 'en_us', '19', '', '{\"typeId\":\"5\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Plumbing\",\"slug\":\"plumbing\",\"postDate\":1471094280,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>Plumbing is a three-year, nine-trimester program.<br><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><strong>When:<\\/strong>&nbsp;Tuesday and Thursday nights 6:30-9:00 p.m.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Plumbers design, install and repair all kinds of systems for water, waste, drainage, sprinklers, steam, gas, heating and cooling in residential, commercial and manufacturing applications. Plumbers also installfixtures such as sinks, toilets, showers, bathtubs, dishwashers and water heaters. Plumbers connect all types of pipes and tubing, while following strict safety procedures and building codes.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Moore Tech\'s plumbing program teaches beginning students everything necessary to enter the plumbing profession. It also prepares existing plumbing employees to advance in the profession. Each student takes one course per term, a total of three courses per year, for three years, a total of nine courses before graduation. Beginning with the first term,&nbsp;Introduction to Plumbing, a student spends 84 hours each term in classroom and lab activities. Students learn all phases of plumbing, including systems design, appliances and fixtures, liquid and gas distribution systems, piping, soldering, brazing and welding, trouble-shooting and repair, reading blueprints and understanding plumbing codes.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>For trimester dates,&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.williamrmoore.org\\/admissions\\/academic-calendar\\/index.html\\\">see our calendar<\\/a>.&nbsp;<\\/p><p><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.williamrmoore.org\\/sites\\/default\\/files\\/gainfulemployment\\/plumbing-2012-13.pdf\\\"><\\/a><\\/p>\",\"32\":\"<p><strong>What are the chances of getting a job when I graduate?<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>This new program began in the current college year 2013-2014.<br>No one has completed the three year program during the reporting period.<br><strong>The college is accredited by Council on Occupational Education and has been for over 40 years.<\\/strong><\\/p>\",\"24\":\"(CIP) Code 46.0503 Plumbing Technology\\/Plumber\",\"20\":\"\",\"31\":\"\",\"30\":\"<p><strong>The college does not participate in any type of loan programs.&nbsp;<\\/strong>For students completing the program,&nbsp;the amount of loan debt for program graduates is shown below:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul><li><strong>Federal loans: none<\\/strong><\\/li><li><strong>Private education loans: none<\\/strong><\\/li><li><strong>Institutional financing plan: none<\\/strong> (Students pay for each trimester before beginning the next trimester.<\\/li><\\/ul>\",\"7\":\"100\",\"21\":\"Plumbing\",\"23\":\"Three year night program (9 Trimesters)\",\"22\":\"Certificate\",\"27\":{\"110\":{\"type\":\"question\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"How much does the Plumbing program cost?\",\"answer\":\"<p>Tuition and fees: $7695<\\/p>\"}},\"111\":{\"type\":\"question\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"question\":\"What other costs are associated with this program?\",\"answer\":\"<p>Books and supplies: $0 (Books and supplies are included in tuition and fees.)<br><strong>The college does not offer on-campus housing<\\/strong><br><strong>Financial Assistance is not available for this program.<\\/strong><br>Night programs do not qualify for financial aid.<\\/p>\"}}},\"5\":[\"29\"],\"18\":\"Plumbers design, install and repair all kinds of systems for water, waste, drainage, sprinklers, steam, gas, heating and cooling in residential, commercial and manufacturing applications. Plumbers also install fixtures such as sinks, toilets, showers, bathtubs, dishwashers and water heaters. Moore Tech\'s plumbing program teaches beginning students everything necessary to enter the plumbing profession. It also prepares existing plumbing employees to advance in the profession.\",\"45\":\"Moore Tech\'s plumbing program teaches beginning students everything necessary to enter the plumbing profession, or prepare existing plumbers to advance in the profession.\",\"6\":\"47-2152.02\",\"25\":\"(SOC) Code: 47-2152.02 Plumbers\",\"33\":\"Plumbers\",\"19\":[\"123\"],\"3\":\"\"}}', '2016-08-15 12:27:46', '2016-08-15 12:27:46', '20acca29-fc7d-40d3-ad6d-e18af76b82f5'),
 ('193', '24', '4', '1', 'en_us', '7', '', '{\"typeId\":\"5\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Welding\",\"slug\":\"welding\",\"postDate\":1470534600,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p><strong>The Moore Tech Welding Program<\\/strong>&nbsp;requires persons who possess good manual dexterity, good eyesight, and good eye-to-hand coordination. They should be able to concentrate on detailed work for long periods of time. Because welding processes differ and are used for a wide variety of purposes, the equipment welders use and the skill levels vary.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Job descriptions vary from highly skilled manual welders who can use both gas and electric arc welding equipment, and welders who plan their work from drawings or other specifications to those of unskilled welding machine tenders who simply press a button to start a machine. Skilled welders know the characteristics of different types of metals and can weld in various positions. Welders who build ships and maintenance welders are examples of skilled welders.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Moore Tech\\u2019s Welding Program is taught in one of the most extensive and complete welding labs in the south. It includes instruction in electric arc welding, plasma arc cutting, oxyacetylene cutting, oxyacetylene welding, (both ferrous, and nonferrous metals,) TIG (Tungsten Inert Gas) & MIG (Metal Inert Gas). The student is taught to identify and use various types of welding equipment, including the characteristics and techniques used in fabricating and assembling metal parts. An important aspect of the program is teaching the individual to read and follow directions.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>This program is designed for individuals who want to become professional welders. It provides the student with a working knowledge of the. The program also is design